@node accegb "Direct access"

  As another  interesting innovation  we have the  possibility of  which a
file of sound or graph,  it is visualized or reproduced by the Eye Viewer,
this it obtains  by means of the attached icons to the files,  to which it
will have that to indicate  in its "Default Tool" the route where you have
installed the program.

  Example: We have an  attached icon to a  graphical file,  him we pulsate
and not it  calls to the Eye Viewer,  showing the typical mistake, to this
icon  we  give  him "Information"  and it  will  open  us  the  window  of
properties of the  icon in "Default Tool"  we indicate him the route where
you should have installed the Eye Viewer, in the folder of icons there are
icons for default, these have as route as default:
  SYS:Utilities/Eye Viewer/Eye Viewer
In case of  having  installed  in  another  place,  editing the  route and
writing in its place  the new one, if we do not do this, the Direct Access
by means of icons it will not work.

  Notices: Also in order that the direct access  works from icons, we have
that to have  the options  activated of "Find images,  sounds or musical",
for that if not, the  Eye Viewer will  not show or  reproduce the  file in
question, since for default he thinks that it is not activated for it.

@endnode
@node teclgb "Keyboard"

  We dispose of the following short-cuts of keyboard to facilitate the use.

 1. The arrow keys up-down for move for the list of files.
 2. Enter for fit the images.
 3. ESC for the search in the option of find files.
 4. Keys + and -. We can to extend or to reduce the zoom for the images.

@endnode
@node botogb "Buttons"

  In the  environment of  the program there are  the following buttons and
dialogue box of text.

  "Directory": Pulsating  on it,  the window  of search  is opened  of the
  directories with the files to showing.

  " " To fit images: Activating this option, the images that appear on the
  screen of the Eye Viewer, they are represented to a proportional size to
  the original size.

  Play and Stop's buttons: Stop or Play the sounds,  on having  moved with
  the  arrow  keys  or the  mouse  pointer,  for  the  name of  some  file
  automatically it reproduces the sound.

  Texts´ box :
    Directory: It shows information of  the directory where  you are, with
    everything the route.
    Next  to  "To fit images"  a  box  of  text  appears  where  us  shows
    information of the selected file:  name, type of file,  size in pixels
    in case of graphs and size in KB.

@endnode
@node menugb "Menu"

  Here we can to find the following options:

   - Folder: Here we  select the  folder where  we have the  files that we
     want to see or to listen.

   - Screen: Here we have two new options.
     * Use screen of the workbench.  We can  to select that the Eye Viewer
       works inside the environment of the Workbench.
     * Use own screen.  We can  to select  that the Eye Viewer works on an
       own screen, where we can to choose the way and resolution.

   - Exit: To exit of program.

@endnode
@node opciongb "Options"

  This is the  option heart of the program,  here is where  we can to form
the options that promote the Eye Viewer.

  Here we can to find the following options:

   - Find images: Activating this option,  it will search  graphical files
     as lbm, jpg, png and gif, etc.

   - Find sounds: Activating this option,  it will search  sonorous files,
     are these wav, 8SVX, aiff.

   - Fing songs: Activating this option, it will search musical files, are
     these mod, mp3, mp2.

 Notices: Here we can to play with the possibility that search us  for one
     directory, only images,  only sounds, only musical; or one mixture of
     them, images and sounds,  images and musical,  sounds and musical; or
     that search  for all of them.   Important for  the Access Direct from
     icons we have to  have the option activated,  if not Eye  Viewer will
     not show or reproduce it.

   - Include subfolders: Activating  this option,  the program will search
     for all the subdirectories  of the chosen directory  the files, if we
     do not activate only it will search for the chosen directory.

   - Find files for its name: Here we have two new options.
     *Activate search: Activating this option we will begin the process of
      search.
     *Enter file name: It opens  a new  window us  where we  introduce the
      complete or  semicomplete name  of the  file,  for which  we want to
      search for the hard disk or folder.
     Steps to continuing to search for a file:
      1. Introducing name is this completely, briefly, extension or number
         in capital letters or small letters.
      2. To activate the option "To activate search".
      3. Choose the directory  where to  initiate the search  pulsating in
         button or in the menu "Folder".
      4. Once finished  the search,  to deactivate the option of "Activate
         search", if it we do not deactivate, the program it will not stop
         searching  files that  coincide with  the pattern  of search, not
         allowing to visualize or to reproduce the rest of files.

   - Auto-Stop for sounds and musical: This option if  we do  not activate
     when the program reproduces  a sound or music, this it would not stop
     and file would be reproduced indefinitely.

   - To see: This option allows to  select the way of  visualization of us
     tree  of the directories  being able  to choose  between  way text or
     miniatures between the following options:
     *For lists: List of text with the name of the files of it folder.
     *For miniatures: Very  useful  when  in  the  directory  that  we are
      exploring it  contains  images, presenting  the  miniatures together
      with its name, resolution and size.

   - Size of the miniatures: If we  choose  the option to  see the tree of
     directory with miniatures we can to choose the size of these:
     *100%: Maximum size of the miniature.
     *75%: Suitable size of the miniature.
     *50%: The half of the maximum size of the miniature.
     *25%: Minimal size of the miniature.

   - Unit AHI: Now we  can to select the  unit AHI for which  we want that
     the sound goes out, being able to choose among 0, 1, 2 and 3.

   - Big pointers of mouse: This  option  is  thought  for  resolutions of
     screen small or well for people who wants the big pointer or small.

   - Speed of the scroll: Here we have two new options.
     *Increase speed: It increases the speed of  displacement of one image
      when this is bigger than the window of showing graphs.
     *Decrease speed: It diminishes the speed of displacement of the image.

   - Retard between photos: This option  allows to select a delay, thought
     for Amigas rapid and in order that on having pulsated on  the name of
     a file or a  miniature,  we avoid that  if we pulsate  on another the
     previous  one we do not  see her if not that in  his place we see one
     sparkle of the image. It has the following options:
     *Increase delay: It increases the delay in a Bruto.
     *Diminish delay: It diminishes the delay in a Bruto.
       (Bruto imaginary unit of time dedicated to our pet)

   - Smoothed in 8 bit: This  option  only works at the  modes of 8 bit in
     cards  that it support;  showing the  graphs with one  palette of 256
     colors; in the rest it does not have any result.
     These are the options that is open.
     * None: It does not apply any filter.
     * Floyd-Steinberg: It applies the filter using these algorithms.
     * Random: Filtered random rapid but of bad quality.
     * EDD: Filtered EDD.

   - Save preferences: This option since it indicates save the preferences
     of the program, like are the activated  options, the modifications in
     Slideshow's option like is the variation of time and directory.

@endnode
@node edicgb "Edition"

  Here we can to think the following options  that give him great power to
"Goya":

   - Copy file: This option allows to copy a file.
     A window will be opened with the following buttons:
     "Remove": Delete  destiny directory  of a list of favorites  with the
      most frequent directories of copy.
     "Remove all": Delete all the directories of the list of favorites.
     "Folder": Press this button we search a directory of destiny to where
      to copy the file.
     "Copy": Press this button copies the file.
     "Copy icon": Activate  this option will copy the icon attached to the
      file.
     "Cancel": We cancel the copy of the file.

   - Move file: This option allows to move  a file and is identical to the
     option of "Copy file",  unless  instead of  the button  "Copy" is the
     button of "Move".

   - Delete file: This option allows to delete  a file when  him we select
     with the arrows keys  or the pointer  of the mouse,  when you pressed
     the  option  will  be   opened  one  window  of  message  asking  for
     confirmation for him to delete.

   - Rename file: This option allows to rename a file.
     A window is opened  with a text  box with the  original name of file,
     where we can overwriting the new name, and after pulsating the button
     of "OK" the file will appear with the new name.

  To copy several files due to the limitations of the program, there is an
interesting trick, which consists, in not to close the window of "Copy" or
"Move",  and  to be selecting  with the  mouse pointer  every file,  which
besides  it will show us,  and when we press  the button  "Copy/Move" will
copy/move the file.

  The most useful innovation that  there presents this  Eye Viewer Goya is
that when we copy or  move a file to  a directory  and inside him there is
another file with the same name,  is opened a new window where us it shows
the  information and name of both files,  in case they are graphical files
besides  it will show  us two miniatures with the two images to compare if
they are equal; we have the following buttons available:
 "Replace": Replaces the file destine for that we want to copy.
 "Cancel": Cancels the operation of copy/move.
 "Rename": On this button a box of text appears, with the name of the file
  origin,  in order that we rename him  and this way not to save  the file
  origin on  the file destine;  when we  write the new name  we will press
  this button and the origin file will copy with the new name.
It is necessary to highlight that on every black window or with miniature,
us  it  informs  about  the  type of  file  that  it is,  size in KB,  and
resolution in pixels for the graphical files.

@endnode
@node favogb "Favorites"

  Here we can to find the following options:

   - Add favorites: Pulsating  in this option  automatically we add to the
     list of favorites the directory where we are.
   - Edit favorites: Pulsating  in this option  it opens a  window us with
     the following buttons:
     "Remove": Eliminate a directory of the list of favorites.
     "Remove all": Eliminate all the directories of the list of favorites.
     "Sort by name": Arrange the list of favorites alphabetical.
     "Move up": We  can to  move  above a  directory  inside  the  list of
      favorites.
     "Move down": We can  to move  below a  directory  inside the  list of
      favorites.
     "Add to favorites": Press this button we add the directory in that we
      are to the list of favorites.
     "OK": Press this button we validate the changes that we have done.
   - Favorites list:  Here  there  appears  a  list  of   our  directories
     favorites.

  Automatically it saves our  list of favorites, when we pulsate button of
"Add to favorites" or when we should edit the list.

@endnode
@node zoomgb "Zoom"

  Here we can to find the following options:

   - Increase size +: We increase the size of the zoom, also we can to use
     the key +.

   - Diminish size -: We diminish the size of the zoom, also we can to use
     the key -.

   - Original size: It comes back to the size in which we were visualizing
     the graph. If the button "To fit images" is activated, the image will
     come back to the original size, in that screen resolution.

@endnode
@node mirr "Mirror"

  Here we can to find the following options:

   - Flip horizontal: It does a horizontal rotation of the image.

   - Flip vertical: It does a vertical rotation of the image.

@endnode
@node slidegb "Slideshow"

  Here we can to find the following options:

   - Begin the Slideshow: Obviously to begin the Slideshow.

   - Time between files: Here we  can to  select the  time of wait between
     the load  of a file and the next;  the time is  expressed in seconds,
     being the minimum 1 and the maximum 59.

   - Loop: Activating  this option  the slide  repeats herself  infinitely
     even that we press the ESC key.

   - Screen mode: Here we have two new options.
     * See on full screen: Show the slideshow to complete screen, if we do
       not activate this option,  the slideshow will appear inside  of the
       window of visualization of the program.
     * You select a resolution: Here  we select  the graphical  resolution
       for the slideshow start from that we have in our Amiga.

  The Slideshow can be with graphs,  sounds or musical,  or with a mixture
of all.

  Notices: When  you will form  the slideshow,  so much in  time or screen
resolution,  is  necessary  to  save  the  preferences  in  "Options--Save
preferences".

@endnode
@node infogb "Information"

  A window is opened,  where it shows us basic information of the program,
authors, version, language, and if it is registered and to whom.

  And now  also a window is opened being  grateful for their collaboration
disinterested,  to all  those  persons who  have dedicated  their time and
strengthen in to make this program possible.

@endnode

;####################  GUÍA EN FRANCÉS  ####################
@node franc "Français"

                  Eye Viewer Goya

   @{"  " link quoi}   Qu'est l'Eye Viewer?
   @{"  " link cond}   Requis.
   @{"  " link emploie}   Comment l'utiliser?
   @{"  " link email}   E-Mailware?
   @{"  " link evol}   Évolutions.
   @{"  " link contactes}   Contact.
   @{"  " link merci}   Remerciements.

@endnode

@node quoi "Qu'est l'Eye Viewer"

  Qu'est Eye Viewer?  Eye Viewer  est un  programme  pour  explorer  votre
disque  dur ŕ la recherche des  graphiques  et des sons;  en utilisant les
datatypes  pour chaque  format,  montrant les images ŕ  l'intérieur  de la
fenętre du programme et de jouer les sons ou de la musique.

  Outre explorer nous avons les options pour  manoeuvrer les images et les
sons; nous pouvons les copier,  les effacer, les déplacer et les renommer;
pour les  images nous pouvons se  déplacer  ŕ l'intérieur  pour la voir au
complet quand celle-ci dépasse la taille de l'écran de l'Eye Viewer, comme
l'options  pour tourner l'image;  en  cas de sons  nous avons  l'option de
jouer et arręter  en options de base pour  pouvoir ętre en mesure de jouer
ou d'arręter le son ou la musique que nous écoutons.
  En outre nous pouvons employer l'Eye Viewer Goya  en présentation de nos
images, sons et music préférés.

  L'Eye Viewer  qui vient en ce paquet  est sans s'enregistrement laissant
visualiser  seulement  16 images;  une  fois  qu'enregistré  vous  pourrez
l'apprécier sans restrictions.

  Disponible dans les langues suivantes:
    1. Espagnol.
    2. Anglais.
    3. Croate.
    4. Français.
    5. L'allemand.
    6. Italiano.

@endnode

@node cond "Requis"

  L'Amiga ou UAE, ŕ besoin des datatypes pour les prochains formats:
  Graphiques:  BMP, GIF, IFF, JPG, LBM, PBM, PCX, PGM, PIC, PNG, PNM, PSD,
               PPM, QRT, TGA, TIF.
  Sons: 8SVX, SVX, MAUD, WAV.
  Musiques: MOD, MP3, MP2.

Les librairies:
  mpega pour jouer les fichiers mp3-mp2
  render v.16
  guigfx v.30
  mathtrans

AHI.
CPU 68020 ou supérieur;
Workbench 3.1, Amiga O.S. 3.5-3.9.
AGA ou carte graphique.

  100% Compatible avec MorphOS 1.4.5

  NOTE: Eye Viewer ne  fonctionne pas sur  Amiga O.S. 4.0, AmiKit, ni avec
des Amiga ayant Directory Opus Magellan.

@endnode

@node emploie "Comment l'utiliser"

  Pour employer  l'Eye Viewer il  est nécessaire  de l'avoir  installé sur
votre  disque  dur,  aussi  vous  avez  besoin  de  la  clef pour  pouvoir
l'employer sans restrictions.

  La gestion de l'Eye Viewer est trčs facile,  nous allons vous expliquer,
ce que font les boutons et les options des menus.

  Accčs direct a l' Eye Viewer.
 @{"  " link accefr} Accčs direct.

  Comment employer les racourcis du clavier et les boutons
 @{"  " link teclfr} Clavier    @{"  " link botofr} Boutons


  Les menus.
 @{"  " link menufr} Menu       @{"  " link opcionfr} Options    @{"  " link edicfr} Édition        @{"  " link favofr} Favoris

